description: The European Union on Monday pledged to spend an initial 7.7 billion euros ($8.39 billion) on humanitarian aid in 2024, less than the previous year despite soaring needs in Gaza and elsewhere.
title: EU pledges 7.7 billion euros towards global needs in 2024

description: An Arizona migrant shelter that has housed thousands of asylum seekers plans to halt most operations in two weeks when funding from Washington runs out, a problem for towns along the border where officials fear a surge in homelessness and extra costs.
title: Arizona county faces 'homelessness on steroids' as migrant shelter funds run out

description: Azeri President Ilham Aliyev said on Sunday his country is "closer than ever" to a peace with Armenia, half a year after Azerbaijan recaptured its Karabakh region from its ethnic Armenian majority, prompting a mass exodus of ethnic Armenians.
title: Azeri president says peace with Armenia is closer than ever

description: U.S. President Joe Biden will speak to Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Monday, according to a person familiar with the matter, after relations were strained further by criticism from the top Senate Democrat.
title: Biden, Israel's Netanyahu to speak on Monday, source says

description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken said on Monday technology should be employed to sustain democratic values in the face of efforts by authoritarian and repressive regimes to deploy technology to undermine democracy and human rights.
title: Blinken says authoritarian regimes using tech to undermine democracy

description: Bulgarian Foreign Minister Mariya Gabriel of the center-right GERB party agreed on Monday to form a new government, following the resignation of Prime Minister Nikolai Denkov on March 5.
title: Bulgarian foreign minister Mariya Gabriel agrees to form new government

description: Canadian legislators are due on Monday to vote on a non-binding motion backing Palestinian statehood that has drawn condemnation from Israel and that could deepen splits inside the ruling Liberal Party.
title: Canada parliament to vote on motion backing Palestinian statehood

description: Chile's economy experienced a slight expansion of 0.1% in the fourth quarter of 2023 compared to the previous quarter, according to data released by the country's central bank on Monday, a figure slightly below market consensus.
title: Chile's GDP slightly rises in Q4, beats annual forecast

description: China will consider taking part in a peace conference aimed at ending the war in Ukraine which neutral Switzerland plans to host in the coming months, the Asian country's ambassador to Bern was quoted as saying on Monday.
title: China considers taking part in Swiss Ukraine peace talks, ambassador says

description: China says it wants to strengthen communications with New Zealand and work to maintain peace and stability in the region as the foreign ministers of the two countries met on Monday.
title: China foreign minister willing to strengthen communications with New Zealand

description: China rebuked South Korea on Monday for Taiwan's participation in a U.S.-backed democracy summit in Seoul, where the island's Digital Minister Audrey Tang delivered an unannounced video message.
title: China protests Taiwan minister's role at Seoul summit backed by U.S.

description: China's embassy in Singapore on Monday urged its citizens in the city-state to stay away from all forms of betting, saying gambling overseas violates Chinese laws.
title: China warns citizens in Singapore to stay away from gambling

description: Chinese military and state-run media on Sunday accused the United States of threatening global security, days after a Reuters report which found Elon Musk's SpaceX was building hundreds of spy satellites for a U.S. intelligence agency.
title: China's military, state media slam U.S. after Reuters report on SpaceX spy satellites

description: Chinese President Xi Jinping on Monday congratulated Vladimir Putin on winning another term as Russia's president and said China was set to maintain close communication with Russia to promote their partnership, according to Chinese state media.
title: China's Xi congratulates Putin on win, set to develop their ties

description: Former Australian Prime Minister Paul Keating, a prominent supporter of China who has criticised Australia's AUKUS nuclear submarine deal with the U.S., said he would meet Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi this week in a bid to improve bilateral ties.
title: Chinese foreign minister to meet former Australia PM Keating on visit

description: Egypt's foreign minister said on Monday the U.S. should make clear to Israel what the consequences of a military push into the south Gaza city of Rafah on the border with Egypt would be, after Washington voiced opposition to such a move.
title: Egypt: US should make clear to Israel consequences of Rafah operation

description: European Union foreign ministers agreed in principle on Monday to impose sanctions on Israeli settlers for attacking Palestinians in the West Bank and to add further sanctions on members of Palestinian Islamist group Hamas.
title: EU agrees on sanctions on Hamas, violent West Bank settlers

description: EU foreign policy chief Josep Borrell said on Monday that Israel is provoking famine in Gaza and using starvation as a weapon of war, an accusation Israel's foreign minister rejected.
title: EU's Borrell says Israel is provoking famine in Gaza

description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol joined U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken and other foreign officials this week in calling for measures to counter digital threats to freedom as Seoul hosted the Summit for Democracy.
title: Explainer: Why is South Korea hosting a 'Summit for Democracy'?

description: Famine is expected between now and May in the north of the Gaza Strip, a U.N.-backed report said on Monday, after more than five months of war which have shattered the Palestinian territory, killed thousands and cut off supplies.
title: Famine expected by May in Gaza, says U.N.-backed report

description: France said on Monday the re-election of Russian President Vladimir Putin took place amid repression, and it praised the many Russians who had peacefully protested against the election.
title: France condemns vote in Ukraine's regions occupied by Russia

description: Gambian lawmakers were due on Monday to vote on a proposal to repeal a ban on female genital mutilation (FGM), which if approved would mark a rare setback for efforts to criminalise the practice.
title: Gambian lawmakers to vote on repealing female genital mutilation ban

description: Food shortages in parts of the Gaza Strip have already far exceeded famine levels, and mass death is now imminent without an immediate ceasefire and surge of food into areas cut off by fighting, the global hunger monitor said on Monday.
title: Gaza suffers famine-level shortages, mass death imminent, UN-backed monitor says

description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz will not congratulate Russian President Vladimir Putin for his re-election in a vote viewed by Berlin as neither free nor fair, a German government spokesperson said on Monday.
title: Germany's Scholz won't congratulate Putin on election win - spokesperson

description: Gunmen in Nigeria have kidnapped at least 87 people, including women and children in Kaduna state, residents and police said on Monday, in a fresh attack after an armed gang seized 286 students and staff from a school in early March.
title: Gunmen kidnap at least 87 in Nigeria's Kaduna state

description: The head of the International Atomic Energy Agency Rafael Grossi met Iraq's prime minister in Baghdad on Monday as part of a visit to help the country develop a peaceful nuclear programme.
title: IAEA to help Iraq develop peaceful nuclear programme, agency head says

description: An independent Russian vote monitoring group said on Monday that the presidential election that Vladimir Putin won in a landslide with nearly 90% of the vote was the most fraudulent and corrupt in the country's history.
title: Independent Russian vote monitor says election was a mockery

description: Israel has asked the International Court of Justice (ICJ) not to issue emergency orders for it to step up humanitarian aid to Gaza to address a looming famine, dismissing South Africa's request to do so as "morally repugnant".
title: Israel asks World Court not to order new measures over Gaza hunger

description: Israel will send a high-level delegation headed by its Mossad chief to Qatar on Monday for mediated talks with Hamas designed to secure a six-week Gaza truce under which the Palestinian militants would free 40 hostages, an Israeli official said.
title: Israel to offer six-week Gaza truce for 40 hostages in Qatar talks, Israeli official says

description: Israeli forces have killed 20 Palestinian gunmen in Gaza's Al Shifa hospital and apprehended dozens of suspected militants, the Israeli military said on Monday.
title: Israeli forces kill 20 gunmen in Gaza's Shifa hospital, military says

description: The Israeli military said on Monday its troops raided the compound of Gaza's Al-Shifa Hospital, in an operation Palestinian health authorities said had caused multiple casualties and set off a fierce fire in one of the buildings.
title: Israeli military says troops raid Gaza's Shifa Hospital

description: The Jordanian army said on Monday its air defence radar system had detected suspicious aerial movements from an unknown source along the border with Syria, which a regional security source said were most probably missiles fired by pro-Iranian militias from Iraq.
title: Jordan army detects suspicious aerial movement near Syria border

description: The Kremlin said on Monday that President Vladimir Putin's re-election showed the Russian people were consolidated around him and that Moscow was not interested in Washington's criticism as the United States was de-facto at war with Russia in Ukraine.
title: Kremlin says Russia is consolidated around Putin, dismisses West's criticism

description: The Kremlin said on Monday that the only way to protect Russian territory from Ukrainian attacks was to create a buffer zone that would put Russian regions beyond the range of Ukrainian fire.
title: Kremlin says the only way to protect Russia is to create a buffer zone with Ukraine

description: The United Nations humanitarian coordinator said on Monday an Israeli assault on Rafah would leave Gaza aid distribution "broken" as the organisation would be unable to prepare enough supplies for the already displaced people fleeing the area.
title: Looming Rafah incursion would 'break' Gaza aid distribution, UN says

description: A fact-finding mission mandated by the United Nations said on Monday the death of Mahsa Amini in custody of Iran's morality police was "unlawful" and caused by violence and that women in the country remain subjected to wide-ranging discrimination.
title: Mahsa Amini's death in Iran custody was 'unlawful', says UN mission

description: Malaysia's former Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad was discharged from hospital on Monday nearly three months after he was admitted for an infection, his office said on Monday.
title: Malaysia's former PM Mahathir discharged from hospital after infection

description: The number of new marriages in China jumped 12.4% in 2023 from a year earlier, reversing a downtrend that has lasted for almost a decade as more youth tied the knot after delaying their nuptials due to the COVID-19 pandemic.
title: More Chinese tied the knot in 2023, lifting marriage rates for first time in nine years

description: Morocco's first legal cannabis harvest was 294 metric tons in 2023, after the country approved its cultivation and export for medicine and industrial uses, cannabis regulator ANRAC said.
title: Morocco reports first legal cannabis harvest of 294 metric tons

description: New Zealand’s prime minister Christopher Luxon intends to travel to China in the coming months following meetings with China’s Foreign Minister Wang Yi in New Zealand this week.
title: New Zealand Prime Minister Luxon intends visit to China

description: Nine people were arrested after a police station in the Paris suburb of La Courneuve was attacked late on Sunday evening following clashes between youths and police forces, the head of the Paris police said on Monday.
title: Nine arrested after Paris suburban police station attacked

description: North Korea fired a ballistic missile into the sea on Monday for the first time in two months, at a time when U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken was visiting Seoul to attend a conference hosted by President Yoon Suk Yeol on advancing democracy.
title: North Korea fires ballistic missile as South hosts democracy conference

description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un has overseen firing drills by artillery units in the western region involving "newly-equipped super-large" multiple rocket launchers, state media KCNA said on Tuesday.
title: North Korea's Kim oversees firing drills with 'super-large' rocket launchers, state media says

description: Polish farmers blocked two border crossings with Germany on Monday, local police said, as protests against European Union environmental regulations and cheap imports sweep the bloc.
title: Polish farmers block two border crossings with Germany

description: Hundreds in Cuba's second-largest city, Santiago, took to the streets late Sunday in a rare public protest, according to social media and official reports, and Cuban President Miguel Diaz-Canel called for an "atmosphere of tranquility and peace."
title: Protest erupts in eastern Cuba amid blackouts, food shortages

description: A day after securing a new six-year term, Russian President Vladimir Putin appeared briefly at an open-air concert on Red Square on Monday to mark the 10th anniversary of Russia's annexation of Crimea from Ukraine.
title: Putin greets Moscow rally after election win

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin warned the West on Monday that a direct conflict between Russia and the U.S.-led NATO military alliance would mean the planet was one step away from World War Three but said hardly anyone wanted such a scenario.
title: Putin warns the West a Russia-NATO conflict is just one step from World War Three

description: Italian Deputy Prime Minister Matteo Salvini distanced himself on Monday from Western leaders' critical response to Vladimir Putin's landslide victory in Russia's presidential election, saying the voters' verdict must be accepted.
title: Russians vote for Putin must be accepted, Italy's Salvini says

description: The election in Russia was not a real election, German Foreign Minister Annalena Baerbock said on Monday.
title: Russia's election wasn't a real election, Germany's Baerbock says

description: Set against miles of mesmerizing sand dunes, Namibia's seaside resort town of Swakopmund is seeing a boom in sandboarding, buoyed by a near-doubling of the numbers of cruise liners docking at nearby Walvis Bay last year.
title: Sandboarding makes a post-COVID comeback in Namibia desert town

description: Seven bodies were found in Petion Ville in the Ouest Department of Haiti, a Reuters source on site said, confirming earlier media reports.
title: Seven bodies found in Petion-Ville, Haiti

description: Habip Yapar felt lucky that his home in southern Turkey withstood last year's devastating earthquake. Then a text message appeared on his phone in October telling him the government was taking ownership of the apartment.
title: Shock and confusion as Turkey seizes earthquake survivors' homes

description: China's rapidly aging population is fuelling a promising and fast-growing market for companies providing recreational classes and activities for the elderly middle class, from yoga to African drumming and smartphone photography.
title: Silver lining: Tutoring the elderly is growing fast in China

description: Somali police and international navies were preparing on Monday to attack a commercial ship that was hijacked by pirates last week, the Puntland region's police force said, two days after Indian commandos rescued another cargo vessel held by pirates.
title: Somali forces, foreign navies prepare attack on hijacked ship, police say

description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol on Monday called fake news and disinformation based on AI and digital technology threats to democracy, as his country hosted a gathering of senior global officials including from Britain, the EU and the United States.
title: South Korea's Yoon warns of tech threat to democracy at summit

description: Spanish police have arrested three people over the deaths of five migrants who were deliberately forced off a speedboat last November, just off an Atlantic ocean beach in Cadiz in southern Spain, the Interior Ministry said on Monday.
title: Spanish police arrest three over death of migrants thrown from boat

description: Afghanistan's Taliban said on Monday that Pakistan carried out two air strikes in Afghan territory, killing five women and three children, with a spokesman condemning the strikes as a violation of sovereignty.
title: Taliban says eight killed in Pakistan's two air strikes in Afghanistan

description: Two tourists from New Zealand were being held in prison in Thailand for allegedly assaulting a police officer on the resort island of Phuket, Thai authorities said.
title: Thailand details two New Zealand tourists for assaulting police officer

description: With politicians pouring in to greet him, a dinner with Thailand's prime minister and a police escort to places he went, billionaire former premier Thaksin Shinawatra looked more like a statesman this weekend than a convicted criminal on parole.
title: Thailand's Thaksin projects power as loyalists cosy up

description: Europe must strengthen its defence capabilities and shift to a "war economy" mode in response to the threat posed by Russia, European Council President Charles Michel said on Monday.
title: To have peace, Europe must prepare for war, EU council president says

description: Donald Trump on Monday asked a Georgia judge to allow him to appeal a ruling keeping the lead prosecutor on the state's criminal case against the former U.S. president over his attempts to overturn his election defeat.
title: Trump wants to appeal Georgia ruling that kept prosecutor on his case

description: British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak said on Monday he still expects the government to begin deporting asylum seekers to Rwanda in the spring, maintaining the original timeline for the scheme which is currently being debated in parliament.
title: UK still aims to begin migrant deportations to Rwanda in the spring, Sunak says

description: Ukrainian air defence systems shot down 17 out of 22 Russian drones over nine Ukrainian regions in an attack that caused a fire in a residential building in the early hours of Monday, officials said.
title: Ukraine downs 17 out of 22 Russia-launched drones, air force says

description: A senior Ukrainian official said on Monday Russian President Vladimir Putin's idea of creating a buffer zone inside Ukrainian territory was a clear indication that Moscow planned to escalate its war in neighbouring Ukraine.
title: Ukraine says Putin's buffer zone comment is a sign of escalation

description: The head of the U.N. Palestinian refugee agency said on Monday the hunger in the Gaza Strip is "man-made".
title: UNRWA chief says hunger in Gaza is "man-made"

description: U.S. Senator Lindsey Graham said on Monday, after meeting Ukraine's president, that he was confident an aid package stalled in the U.S. Congress would soon be approved, but called for aid to take the form of a low-interest, waivable loan.
title: US Senator Graham says Ukraine aid depends on conditions, domestic issues

description: A U.S. government research team found no significant evidence of brain injury among a group of federal employees reporting symptoms of the "Havana syndrome" ailment that emerged in 2016, according to studies published in a medical journal on Monday.
title: US study finds no evidence of Havana syndrome brain injury

description: U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris will meet with Guatemala's new liberal president, Bernardo Arévalo, at the White House next week to discuss bolstering democracy and addressing the "root causes" of migration from Central America, officials told Reuters.
title: U.S. VP Harris to discuss migration with Guatemala's Arévalo at White House

description: Western governments lined up on Monday to condemn Vladimir Putin's landslide election victory as unfair and undemocratic, but China and North Korea congratulated the veteran Russian leader on extending his rule by a further six years.
title: West decries Putin's landslide election win, China congratulates him

description: President Vladimir Putin won a record post-Soviet landslide in Russia's election on Sunday, cementing his grip on power, though thousands of opponents staged a noon protest at polling stations and Western countries said the vote was neither free nor fair.
title: What Putin’s election win tells us about Russia today

description: The World Health Organization chief on Monday voiced concern about the Al Shifa Hospital in northern Gaza after an Israeli raid of the site.
title: WHO chief voices concern over Gaza's Al Shifa Hospital
